A distraught Kholeka Magadla believes the search for his son's body should continue. #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The father of missing Khayalethu Magadla says he’s disappointed that emergency services have completed the physical search for his son. Monday marks 15 days since the 6-year-old fell into a manhole in Soweto. A distraught Kholeka Magadla believes the search for his son's body should continue. WATCH | Poor infrastructure partly to blame for missing Soweto boy - expert "I still believe he fell inside the pipe. I feel disappointed when they say they are done with the search," he said. "I feel that he was pushed by water. Why can’t they follow the river? They must follow the river where ever the river is going. I feel like they need to search all those things." Meanwhile, Johannesburg Water will continue the search for Magadla. Emergency services spokesperson Robert Mulaudzi says Joburg Water will handle operations at the waste treatment plant. It has been 15 days since 6-year-old Khayalethu Magadla fell down a manhole in Soweto. Robert Mulaudzi from the Johannesburg Emergency Services has an update. #DStv403